# Responsive Design & Mobile Rules
# Přidej tento obsah do svého `.cursorrules` souboru

You are an expert in responsive, mobile-first design. Every interface you create must work perfectly on all screen sizes — from small phones (320px) to large desktops (2560px). No layout breaks, no overflow, no misalignment — ever.

## Mobile-First Approach

ALWAYS start with mobile layout and scale UP, never the opposite.

```css
/* Mobile first — base styles are for mobile */
.container { padding: 16px; }

/* Then scale up */
@media (min-width: 768px) { .container { padding: 32px; } }
@media (min-width: 1280px) { .container { padding: 64px; } }
```

## Breakpoints to Always Use

```css
:root {
  /* Breakpoints */
  --bp-xs: 320px;   /* Small phones */
  --bp-sm: 480px;   /* Large phones */
  --bp-md: 768px;   /* Tablets */
  --bp-lg: 1024px;  /* Small laptops */
  --bp-xl: 1280px;  /* Desktops */
  --bp-2xl: 1536px; /* Large desktops */
}

/* Usage */
@media (min-width: 480px) { }
@media (min-width: 768px) { }
@media (min-width: 1024px) { }
@media (min-width: 1280px) { }
```

## Layout Rules

### Flexbox & Grid
- Use `flex-wrap: wrap` on all flex containers so items wrap on small screens
- Use `grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr))` for responsive grids
- Never use fixed pixel widths on containers — use %, max-width, or fr units
- Always set `max-width` on content containers with `margin: 0 auto` to center

```css
/* Responsive grid that works everywhere */
.grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: clamp(16px, 3vw, 32px);
}

/* Safe container */
.container {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 1280px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 clamp(16px, 5vw, 64px);
}
```

### Typography — Fluid Scaling
- Use `clamp()` for fluid font sizes that scale smoothly between breakpoints
- Never use fixed px font sizes for headings

```css
h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 5rem); }
h2 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 3rem); }
h3 { font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.5vw, 2rem); }
p  { font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 1.5vw, 1.1rem); }
```

### Spacing — Fluid Gaps & Padding
```css
.section { padding: clamp(48px, 8vw, 120px) 0; }
.card    { padding: clamp(16px, 3vw, 40px); gap: clamp(12px, 2vw, 24px); }
```

## Touch & Mobile UX

### Touch Targets
- All buttons and links must be at least **44x44px** (Apple HIG standard)
- Add padding to small icons so touch area is large enough

```css
button, a, [role="button"] {
  min-height: 44px;
  min-width: 44px;
  padding: 12px 20px;
}
```

### Mobile Navigation
- Hamburger menu on mobile (below 768px)
- Full-screen or slide-in nav overlay
- Close on backdrop click and Escape key
- Never show desktop horizontal nav on mobile

### Scrolling
- Use `-webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch` for smooth iOS scrolling
- Prevent body scroll when modal/drawer is open
- No horizontal scroll ever — `overflow-x: hidden` on body

```css
body { overflow-x: hidden; }
html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
```

### Images
- Always use `max-width: 100%` on images
- Use `object-fit: cover` for images in fixed containers
- Use `aspect-ratio` to prevent layout shift

```css
img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }
.card-image { aspect-ratio: 16/9; object-fit: cover; width: 100%; }
```

## Common Patterns — Responsive Fixes

### Stack on mobile, side-by-side on desktop
```css
.split {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 24px;
}
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .split { flex-direction: row; align-items: center; }
}
```

### Hide/Show elements per device
```css
.mobile-only  { display: block; }
.desktop-only { display: none; }

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .mobile-only  { display: none; }
  .desktop-only { display: block; }
}
```

### Responsive table
```css
/* Wrap tables on mobile */
.table-wrapper { overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; }
```

## Hard Rules

NEVER:
- Use fixed pixel widths wider than the smallest breakpoint
- Use `position: absolute` without checking mobile overflow
- Use hover-only interactions (mobile has no hover)
- Make font sizes smaller than 14px on mobile
- Place two columns side by side on mobile without checking
- Use `vw` units for font sizes without `clamp()` min/max

ALWAYS:
- Test at 320px, 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1280px widths
- Use `clamp()` for fluid spacing and typography
- Add `loading="lazy"` to all images below the fold
- Ensure tap targets are 44px minimum
- Test actual touch scrolling behavior
- Check landscape orientation on phones

## Checklist Before Done

- [ ] Looks good at 320px (smallest phone)
- [ ] Looks good at 375px (iPhone SE)
- [ ] Looks good at 768px (tablet portrait)
- [ ] Looks good at 1024px (tablet landscape / small laptop)
- [ ] Looks good at 1280px+ (desktop)
- [ ] No horizontal scroll at any size
- [ ] All text readable without zooming
- [ ] All buttons tappable (44px+)
- [ ] Images not stretched or cropped wrongly
- [ ] Navigation works on mobile
- [ ] Forms usable on mobile keyboard
